channel.name: BBC One NL
channel.title: Live: WA World Championship Athletics
channel.desc: Coverage continues of the evening session of day two of the World Athletics Championships, with five gold medals on offer. After over a year out through injury, Jazmin Sawyers will be aiming to make the women's long jump final, and there will be a new world champion in the men's 10,000m as Uganda's Joshua Cheptegei won't be in Tokyo. Then, the fastest man and woman in the world will be crowned, with the finals of the 100m finishing off the second day's action.
